objectives.name: Primary Objective 1
objectives.text: to compare OS in subjects with squamous cell carcinoma of the esophagus.

objectives.name: Primary Objective 2
objectives.text: To compare OS in subjects with PD-L1 Combined Positive Score (CPS)≥10.

objectives.name: Primary Objective 3
objectives.text: To compare OS in all subjects.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective 1
objectives.text: To evaluate the progression free survival (PFS) per RECIST 1.1 assessed by central vendor review in all subjects, when treated with pembrolizumab compared to investigator’s choice of paclitaxel, docetaxel, or irinotecan.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective 2
objectives.text: To evaluate the Objective Response Rate (ORR) per RECIST 1.1 assessed by central vendor review in all subjects, when treated with pembrolizumab compared to investigator’s choice of paclitaxel, docetaxel, or irinotecan.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective 3
objectives.text: To evaluate the PFS and ORR per RECIST 1.1 assessed by central vendor review in subjects with squamous cell carcinoma of the esophagus and subjects with PD-L1 CPS≥10, when treated with pembrolizumab compared to investigator’s choice of paclitaxel, docetaxel, or irinotecan.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective 4
objectives.text: Evaluate the safety and tolerability profile of pembrolizumab in all subjects, when treated with pembrolizumab compared to investigator’s choice of paclitaxel, docetaxel, or irinotecan.

objectives.name: Exploratory Objective 1
objectives.text: To evaluate PFS per irRECIST assessed by blinded central vendor review in all subjects when treated with pembrolizumab 200 mg Q3W compared to investigator’s choice of paclitaxel, docetaxel, or irinotecan.

objectives.name: Exploratory Objective 2
objectives.text: To evaluate efficacy by GEP expression.

objectives.name: Exploratory Objective 3
objectives.text: To explore the concordance of PD-L1 in archival compared to newly obtained tumor tissue.

objectives.name: Exploratory Objective 4
objectives.text: To evaluate score change of health related quality of life using the EORTC QLQ-C30 and the EORTC QLQ-OES18 from baseline among subjects when treated with pembrolizumab 200 mg Q3W compared to investigator’s choice of paclitaxel, docetaxel, or irinotecan.

objectives.name: Exploratory Objective 5
objectives.text: To characterize utilities using EuroQol EQ-5D among subjects when treated with pembrolizumab 200 mg Q3W compared to investigator’s choice of paclitaxel, docetaxel, or irinotecan.

objectives.name: Exploratory Objective 6
objectives.text: To explore the relationship between genetic variation and response to the treatment administered. Variation across the human genome will be analyzed for association with clinical data collected in this study.

endpoints.name: Primary Efficacy Endpoint
endpoints.text: Overall Survival (OS)

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint - PFS
endpoints.text: Progression free survival (PFS) per RECIST 1.1 as assessed by the central imaging vendor

endpoints.text: Objective response rate (ORR) per RECIST 1.1 as assessed by the central imaging vendor

endpoints.name: Safety Endpoint
endpoints.text: Safety and tolerability (toxicities as defined by CTCAE version 4.0, SAEs, and ECIs)

endpoints.name: Exploratory Endpoint - irRECIST
endpoints.text: PFS per irRECIST assessed by blinded central vendor review

endpoints.name: Exploratory Endpoint - GEP
endpoints.text: Efficacy by GEP expression

endpoints.name: Exploratory Endpoint - PD-L1 Concordance
endpoints.text: Concordance of PD-L1 in archival compared to newly obtained tumor tissue

endpoints.name: Exploratory Endpoint - QoL
endpoints.text: Score change of health related quality of life using the EORTC QLQ-C30 and the EORTC QLQ-OES18 from baseline

endpoints.name: Exploratory Endpoint - EQ-5D
endpoints.text: Utilities using EuroQol EQ-5D

endpoints.name: Exploratory Endpoint - Genetic
endpoints.text: Relationship between genetic variation and response to the treatment administered
